[0m[49m[39m  553, 525[0m:[39m[49m **Where it struggles:**
[0m[49m[39m  554, 526[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 555     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - Patients with rare conditions not well-represented in training data
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 556     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - Very early in admission (< 4 hours) when insufficient data has accumulated
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 557     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - Patients whose trajectory changes rapidly (septic shock onset, cardiac arrest)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 558     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - Distinguishing "dying from disease" vs. "dying from treatment withdrawal"
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 559     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - Patients transferred from other facilities (missing historical context)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 560     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - Novel disease presentations (e.g., early COVID-19 before models were retrained)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Patients with rare diagnoses underrepresented in training data (e.g., rare toxicologic exposures)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Very early predictions (first 6 hours) before enough temporal data accumulates
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Patients transferred from other ICUs (missing early trajectory data)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Populations with significant demographic shift from training data
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Cases where withdrawal of life-sustaining treatment is the proximate cause of death (self-fulfilling prophecy)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Rapidly changing clinical status where 4-hour rescoring misses the inflection point
